<h2>Rules for form elements</h2>
<ul>
	<li>You should only ever ask for the information you absolutely need.</li>
	<li>You must not mark mandatory fields with asterisks.</li>
	<li>You may ask for optional information, if so, you must mark the labels of optional fields with ‘(optional)’.</li>
	<li>You must not use forms in sidebars.</li>
	<li>Form elements that use the <code>form-control</code> class will fill the width of their container by default. For form elements that expect short inputs the <code>size</code> attribute combined with the <code>form-control--auto-width</code> can be used to change an elements width.</li>
</ul>

